---
title: Tofu Nasi Goreng with pak choi and bell pepper
description: The name 'nasi goreng' actually means fried rice in both Indonesian and Malay. It's a Southeast Asian favourite that's actually one of Indonesia's national dishes. It's a meal that involves rice, an egg, and an array of other optional elements. This veggie version utilizes crispy tofu as its shining star.
